one\">I am not a woman with a sword, and I don\u2019t live in a soft, watercolor world that\u2019s quickly being overcome by dark, spindly shadows. But I feel like I do. Most days are a fight as I slash back at the abyss that threatens to overwhelm; I have a lot more in common, right now, with <a href=\"https://store.steampowered.com/app/2420660/Neva/\"><em>Neva</em></a>\u2019s striking human character Alba than I expected.</p>\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\"><em>Neva</em>, <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/reviews/2018/11/8/18069254/gris-review-switch-pc-devolver-digital\">Nomada Studio\u2019s follow-up to its widely ", "id": 1322522, "language": null, "link": "https://www.polygon.com/review/465091/neva-review-nomada-devolver-digital", "manual_status_code": 0, "page_rating": 27, "page_rating_contents": 85, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "source__id": 258, "source_url": "https://www.polygon.com/rss/index.xml", "status_code": 0, "tags": [], "thumbnail": null, "title": "Neva, the follow-up to Gris, is devastatingly beautiful", "vote": 0}, {"age": null, "album": "", "artist": null, "bookmarked": false, "comments": [], "date_published": "2024-10-14T11:00:00+00:00", "description": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n<figure>\n\n<img alt=\"The blue-haired main character of Metaphor: ReFantazio alongside his tiny fairy companion Gallica, who is hovering to the left\" data-caption=\"\" data-portal-copyright=\"\" data-has-syndication-rights=\"1\" src=\"https://platform.polygon.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2024/10/ss_527790d51f418e98fb04819221a348103c85a69b.1920x1080.jpg?quality=90&#038;strip=all&#038;crop=0,0,100,100\" />\n\t<figcaption></figcaption>\n</figure>\n<p class=\"has-text-align-none\">Back in April, as part of a <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AMO-eAwvvuY&amp;t=1s\">promotional video about <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em></a>, the game\u2019s director Katsura Hashino quietly dropped a fact (via translator) t